<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName LSID="DAD63D30-357D-53BE-8FEA-5EBACB4FB8AA" authority="C. M. Tian, Q. Yang &amp; N. Jiang" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Synnemasporellaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Flavignomonia C.M. Tian, Q. Yang &amp; N. Jiang</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="0" pageNumber="17">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Synnemasporellaceae" genus="Synnemasporella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Synnemasporella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Synnemasporella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the orange tips of its synnemata.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia rhoigena" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rhoigena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia rhoigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C.M. Tian &amp; Q. Yang
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
The generic name is derived from the colour of synnemata (flavus = yellow) and the genus name 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Gnomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gnomonia" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Gnomonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Sexual morph: not observed. Asexual morph: Conidiomata synnematal. Synnemata long and determinate, growing from host tissue, with brown base and orange tip, straight to curved, parallel, with flat to slightly concave and dark zone of conidiogenous cells and host tissue at their bases. Conidiophores reduced to conidiogenous cells. Conidiogenous cells phialidic, aggregated, hyaline, straight to curved, cylindrical, arranged adjacent to one another at the end of the synnema, producing a single conidium. Conidia cylindrical to oblong, smooth, multiguttulate, hyaline.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included in 
<taxonomicName family="Gnomoniaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="family">Gnomoniaceae</taxonomicName>
based on DNA sequences data. 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Synnemasporellaceae" genus="Synnemasporella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Synnemasporella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Synnemasporella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in forming synnemata (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(33)80010-6" author="Wehmeyer, LE" journalOrPublisher="Biological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B33" refString="Wehmeyer, LE, 1933. .https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(33)80010-6" url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(33)80010-6" year="1933">Wehmeyer 1933</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2018.40.05" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="119 - 134" refId="B7" refString="Fan, XL, Bezerra, JD, Tian, CM, Crous, PW, 2018. Families and genera of diaporthalean fungi associated with canker and dieback of tree hosts. Persoonia 40: 119 - 134" title="Families and genera of diaporthalean fungi associated with canker and dieback of tree hosts." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2018.40.05" volume="40" year="2018">Fan et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, typified with 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Gnomoniaceae" genus="Flavignomonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Flavignomonia rhoigena" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="rhoigena">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Flavignomonia rhoigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Synnemasporellaceae" genus="Synnemasporella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Synnemasporella" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Synnemasporella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by its orange synnematal tips and hyaline conidia (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2018.40.05" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="119 - 134" refId="B7" refString="Fan, XL, Bezerra, JD, Tian, CM, Crous, PW, 2018. Families and genera of diaporthalean fungi associated with canker and dieback of tree hosts. Persoonia 40: 119 - 134" title="Families and genera of diaporthalean fungi associated with canker and dieback of tree hosts." url="https://doi.org/10.3767/persoonia.2018.40.05" volume="40" year="2018">Fan et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
